              "prompt": "You are asked to count the number of inversions in an array (pairs $i<j$ with $A[i]>A[j]$) â€” a measure of how unsorted the array is, used in rank-correlation statistics. Brute force is $\\Theta(n^2)$. Design a divide-and-conquer algorithm in $\\Theta(n\\log n)$ by piggybacking on merge sort. State the divide step, the combine step (the crucial part), and the recurrence.",
