              "hint": "First $h(P)=26 \\bmod 13$. Compute the first window hash directly, then roll with $h' = ((h - T[i]\\cdot 10)\\cdot 10 + T[i+m]) \\bmod 13$, always feeding back the PREVIOUS window's hash. Verify characters on every hash match.",
              "solution": "h(P) = 26 mod 13 = 0. b^(m-1)=10^1=10. Windows of T='235902':\n- '23': 23 mod 13 = 10. 10!=0, skip.\n- roll to '35': ((10 - 2*10)*10 + 5) mod 13 = ((10-20)*10+5) mod 13 = (-95) mod 13. Since 13*8=104, -95+104=9. So 9. 9!=0, skip.\n- roll to '59': ((9 - 3*10)*10 + 9) mod 13 = ((9-30)*10+9) mod 13 = (-201) mod 13. Since 13*16=208, -201+208=7. So 7. skip.\n- roll to '90': ((7 - 5*10)*10 + 0) mod 13 = ((7-50)*10+0) mod 13 = (-430) mod 13. Since 13*34=442, -430+442=12. So 12. skip.\n- roll to '02': ((12 - 9*10)*10 + 2) mod 13 = ((12-90)*10+2) mod 13 = (-778) mod 13. Since 13*60=780, -778+780=2. So 2. h=2 != 0, skip.\nWindow hashes are 10, 9, 7, 12, 2 â€” none equal h(P)=0, so there are no hash hits and no matches (26 indeed does not occur in 235902). No spurious hits arose. (Sanity check on a known match: the substring '26' appears later in the full T; with this small M you would see it hash to 0 and then pass character verification.)"
