              "solution": "(a) Structure (â˜… = is_word):\nroot -> b -> a -> t â˜…(bat) -> c -> h â˜…(batch)\n                         t -> h â˜…(bath)\n              a -> d â˜…(bad)\n     b -> e â˜…(be)\nMore explicitly: from root, child 'b'. From b: child 'a' and child 'e'â˜…(be). From 'a': children 't' and 'd'â˜…(bad). Node 't' is â˜…(bat) and has children 'c' and 'h'â˜…(bath). Node 'c' has child 'h'â˜…(batch).\n(b) Results:\n- search('bat') = True (node exists, is_word set).\n- search('ba') = False (node exists but is_word not set; it's an internal prefix).\n- starts_with('bat') = True (node exists; completions bat, batch, bath hang at or below it).\n- search('batch') = True (full path exists, is_word set).\n- search('bate') = False (after 'bat' there is no child 'e')."
